EKT plugin license note:

The EKT server plugin (Encrypted Key Transport, RFC 8870) is included in
the `flexisip-conference` image for end-to-end encrypted conferences.

The upstream `ENABLE_EKT_SERVER` CMake option in `flexisip-conference`
declares:

> Enable Encrypted Key Transport server. For customers under a proprietary
> license, this functionality is under a specific license.

The plugin's own README, however, declares GNU AGPLv3. This build treats
the plugin as AGPL-compatible and enables it via the build option
`-DENABLE_EKT_SERVER=ON` for the conference package. If you intend to
redistribute the resulting binaries under terms incompatible with AGPLv3,
or operate a hosted service without source disclosure, you may need a
separate license from Belledonne Communications. **This is not legal
advice.**

